==English==
===Verb form===
'''pent'''
# Alternative [[past tense]] of the verb ''to [[pen]]''
===Adjective===
'''pent'''
# [[confined]] in a [[pen]], imprisoned.
#:''My object all sublime
#:''I shall achieve in time —
#:''To let the punishment fit the crime —
#:''The punishment fit the crime;
#:''And make each prisoner '''pent'''
#:''Unwillingly represent
#:''A source of innocent merriment!
#:''Of innocent merriment!'' — W.S. Gilbert, ''The Mikado''.

====Usage note====
While probably archaic, Gilbert's use (in the quote given above) has kept the word current.
